Awards:

2022-23 Mountain West All-Freshman Team

Mountain West Freshman of the Week (Jan. 16, 2023)

2023-24 All-Mountain West First Team

Sophomore | 2023-24:

535 career points in 2023-24 marks the highest scoring single-season performance in Air Force Division I history and is third all time … 197 field goals made claims an Air Force Division I record and falls in fourth all time … 497 attempted field goals for reset the all-time single season record for attempts … 26 attempted baskets at San Diego State (Jan. 3, 2024) tied the Falcon Division I record, set by Riley Snyder against Army on Nov. 13, 2019 …16.7 points per game ranks tenth all time and second in Falcon Division I history … Played in all 32 games, starting in 30 … Playing in a non-traditional point guard role in 2023-24, led Air Force in assists (84), averaging 3.5 per game in conference play, the sixth-best figure in the Mountain West … In the program’s first-ever win at Boise State’s ExtraMile Arena, Perry closed the contest with a team-high 23 points (8-15 FG, 1-3 3FG, 6-6 FT), outscoring the Broncos 8-6 on her own in the second quarter, and scored the Falcons’ final six points in a one-possession affair, including the go-ahead basket with 3.5 seconds to go … Falling against Nevada on Feb. 7, Perry reset her career best, scoring 30 points on 10-20 FG and 4-5 from three, marking just the fifth 30-point output by a Falcon in the past decade and the second this season … In Mountain West play, finished third in scoring average (18.22), seventh in field goal percentage (.418), sixth in assists (3.50), second in free throw percentage (.826), tenth in steals (1.44) and sixth in assist/turnover ratio (1.58) … Possessing 672 career points, Perry is currently on-pace to become Air Force’s 19th all-time career 1000-point scorer.

Freshman | 2022-23:

Was first off the bench in the Falcons’ rotation as a freshman … Appeared in 29 games in 2022-23, averaging 7.1 points per game in 19.0 minutes of play time … Led Air Force in blocked shots, logging 12 on the year … Posted a career-best in points (22) and free throws made (9) against Wyoming (Jan. 11) … Was second among the Falcon roster in free throws made (51) and third in field goal attempts (220).

Before Air Force: Played for Joe Cooper at Seffner Christian Academy…Play4Kay Shootout MVP…MLK Shootout MVP…Class 4A State Champion…Two-time Regional Champion…Three-time District Champion…averaged 16.7 PPG, 6.2 RPG, and 4.1 APG her senior season…Played club for Candace Parker Hoop Dreams Elite.

Personal: Member of cadet squadron 16…Daughter of Mark and Karen Perry…Has two sisters, Maliyah and Mila…Intended major is business management with a minor in Spanish…Born in Bakersfield, CA.
